remarks: A real number larger than the upper bound of a left open right closed interval is not an element of the interval.  (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)
statement:
gtnelioc.a $e |- ( ph -> A e. RR* ) $.
gtnelioc.b $e |- ( ph -> B e. RR ) $.
gtnelioc.c $e |- ( ph -> C e. RR* ) $.
gtnelioc.bltc $e |- ( ph -> B < C ) $.
gtnelioc $p |- ( ph -> -. C e. ( A (,] B ) ) $.
